/wiki/Kazakhstan_women's_national_rugby_: The Kazakhstan women 's national sevens rugby union team is Kazakhstan 's representative in Rugby sevens at an international level . They won Gold at the 2010 Asian Games defeating China in the finals .
/wiki/China_women's_national_rugby_seven: The Chinese women 's national sevens rugby union team are currently the Asian women 's sevens champions .
/wiki/Thailand_women's_national_rugby_se: Thailand 's women 's national rugby sevens team competes at the Asian Games and other sevens tournaments . They were bronze medalists at the 2010 Asian Games .
/wiki/Hong_Kong_women's_national_rugby_s: The Hong Kong women 's sevens rugby union team represents Hong Kong at an international level and plays at the Hong Kong Women 's Sevens and other international sevens tournaments .
/wiki/Japan_women's_national_rugby_seven: The Japan women 's national rugby sevens team has competed in competitions such as the Hong Kong Women 's Sevens . In 2012-13 they played two World Series tournaments , resulting 13th in China . In the 2013-14 season they resulted 7th at São Paulo and 8th at Atlanta . They were not invited to any World Series tournament in 2014-15 . Japan played the full 2015-16 World Series , with a best result of 9th at the Dubai Sevens , and finished 11th in the overall standings . Japan qualified for the 2016 Summer Olympics after winning the 2015 ARFU Women 's Sevens Championships . The team won over Kenya but lost twice to Brazil , finishing 10th in the tournament .
/wiki/Singapore_women's_national_rugby_s: The Singapore women 's national sevens rugby union team is Singapore 's national representative in Rugby sevens .
/wiki/India_women's_national_rugby_seven: The India women 's national sevens rugby union team is India 's national representative in Rugby sevens .
/wiki/South_Korea_women's_national_rugby: South Korea 's women 's national sevens rugby union team represents South Korea in Rugby sevens at international level .
